{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WDnU63JtDwq4zvM3uCVCKq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# Specification: [300] Referral System\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆ## Meta\n     4ŌåÆ\n     5ŌåÆ| Field | Value |\n     6ŌåÆ|-------|-------|\n     7ŌåÆ| Status | Ready |\n     8ŌåÆ| Priority | P1 |\n     9ŌåÆ| Track | Extended |\n    10ŌåÆ| NR_OF_TRIES | 14 |\n    11ŌåÆ\n    12ŌåÆ---\n    13ŌåÆ\n    14ŌåÆ## Overview\n    15ŌåÆ\n    16ŌåÆA Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can set a custom referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 ŌĆö no program changes required.\n    17ŌåÆ\n    18ŌåÆ## User Stories\n    19ŌåÆ\n    20ŌåÆ- As a player, I want to set a custom referral code so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n    21ŌåÆ- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n    22ŌåÆ- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n    23ŌåÆ- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n    24ŌåÆ- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n    25ŌåÆ\n    26ŌåÆ---\n    27ŌåÆ\n    28ŌåÆ## Capability Alignment\n    29ŌåÆ\n    30ŌåÆ- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" ŌåÆ \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n    31ŌåÆ- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n    32ŌåÆ- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n    33ŌåÆ\n    34ŌåÆ## Required Context Files\n    35ŌåÆ\n    36ŌåÆ- `docs/DECISIONS.md` ŌĆö fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n    37ŌåÆ- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` ŌĆö frontend entrypoint\n    38ŌåÆ- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` ŌĆö on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n    39ŌåÆ- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n    40ŌåÆ\n    41ŌåÆ## Contract Files\n    42ŌåÆ\n    43ŌåÆ- No existing mocks ŌĆö this is a new system\n    44ŌåÆ- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n    45ŌåÆ\n    46ŌåÆ---\n    47ŌåÆ\n    48ŌåÆ## System Invariants (v1)\n    49ŌåÆ\n    50ŌåÆThese invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n    51ŌåÆ\n    52ŌåÆ1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n    53ŌåÆ2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n    54ŌåÆ3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n    55ŌåÆ4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n    56ŌåÆ5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n    57ŌåÆ6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n    58ŌåÆ7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n    59ŌåÆ\n    60ŌåÆ---\n    61ŌåÆ\n    62ŌåÆ## Functional Requirements\n    63ŌåÆ\n    64ŌåÆ### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n    65ŌåÆ\n    66ŌåÆAny player with a connected wallet can set a referral code. No eligibility gate ŌĆö open from day one.\n    67ŌåÆ\n    68ŌåÆ**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n    69ŌåÆ\n    70ŌåÆ**Code format:**\n    71ŌåÆ- Player-chosen custom code: 3-16 characters, `[a-z0-9-]`, must be unique\n    72ŌåÆ- No auto-generation ŌĆö the player always picks their own code\n    73ŌåÆ- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n    74ŌåÆ\n    75ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    76ŌåÆ- [ ] Authenticated player can set a referral code via API <!-- gap: routes/referral.ts does not exist -->\n    77ŌåÆ- [ ] Code is always player-chosen, 3-16 chars, validated against `[a-z0-9-]`, unique <!-- gap: no validation logic implemented -->\n    78ŌåÆ- [x] Each player has exactly one active code (setting a new one replaces the old one) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql UNIQUE(wallet) + db.ts:660 upsertReferralCode ON CONFLICT replaces -->\n    79ŌåÆ- [x] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates table + db.ts:637 insertReferralCode -->\n    80ŌåÆ\n    81ŌåÆ### FR-2: Referral Linking\n    82ŌåÆ\n    83ŌåÆWhen a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n    84ŌåÆ\n    85ŌåÆ**Rules:**\n    86ŌåÆ- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n    87ŌåÆ- First code applied wins ŌĆö cannot change referrer\n    88ŌåÆ- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n    89ŌåÆ\n    90ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    91ŌåÆ- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates <!-- gap: no /r/:code route in App.tsx -->\n    92ŌåÆ- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n    93ŌåÆ- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page) <!-- gap: no POST /referral/apply endpoint or profile UI -->\n    94ŌåÆ- [x] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 referee_wallet UNIQUE + db.ts:694 insertReferralLink throws on duplicate -->\n    95ŌåÆ- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected <!-- gap: no API-level validation implemented -->\n    96ŌåÆ- [x] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:17-22 + db.ts:694-701 insertReferralLink -->\n    97ŌåÆ\n    98ŌåÆ### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n    99ŌåÆ\n   100ŌåÆReferred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable ŌĆö every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3b67986-fd78-4b1a-b5f8-3ba5e0f9fe3d","uuid":"9ef68d94-d123-4977-9d09-6681b62b5939","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:17:55.534Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"# Specification: [300] Referral System\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Track | Extended |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 14 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nA Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can set a custom referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 ŌĆö no program changes required.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to set a custom referral code so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n\n---\n\n## Capability Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" ŌåÆ \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `docs/DECISIONS.md` ŌĆö fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` ŌĆö frontend entrypoint\n- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` ŌĆö on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- No existing mocks ŌĆö this is a new system\n- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n\n---\n\n## System Invariants (v1)\n\nThese invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n\n1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n\nAny player with a connected wallet can set a referral code. No eligibility gate ŌĆö open from day one.\n\n**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n\n**Code format:**\n- Player-chosen custom code: 3-16 characters, `[a-z0-9-]`, must be unique\n- No auto-generation ŌĆö the player always picks their own code\n- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Authenticated player can set a referral code via API <!-- gap: routes/referral.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Code is always player-chosen, 3-16 chars, validated against `[a-z0-9-]`, unique <!-- gap: no validation logic implemented -->\n- [x] Each player has exactly one active code (setting a new one replaces the old one) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql UNIQUE(wallet) + db.ts:660 upsertReferralCode ON CONFLICT replaces -->\n- [x] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates table + db.ts:637 insertReferralCode -->\n\n### FR-2: Referral Linking\n\nWhen a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n\n**Rules:**\n- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n- First code applied wins ŌĆö cannot change referrer\n- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates <!-- gap: no /r/:code route in App.tsx -->\n- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page) <!-- gap: no POST /referral/apply endpoint or profile UI -->\n- [x] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 referee_wallet UNIQUE + db.ts:694 insertReferralLink throws on duplicate -->\n- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected <!-- gap: no API-level validation implemented -->\n- [x] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:17-22 + db.ts:694-701 insertReferralLink -->\n\n### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n\nReferred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable ŌĆö every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.","numLines":100,"startLine":1,"totalLines":715}}}
