{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MVhGqtsSy1NDa7C2MfqmWv","type":"tool_result","content":"   100ŌåÆReferred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable ŌĆö every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n   101ŌåÆ\n   102ŌåÆ**Economics:**\n   103ŌåÆ- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n   104ŌåÆ- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n   105ŌåÆ- Fee is charged in full on-chain ŌĆö rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n   106ŌåÆ- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n   107ŌåÆ\n   108ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   109ŌåÆ- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n   110ŌåÆ- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n   111ŌåÆ- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n   112ŌåÆ- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   113ŌåÆ- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n   114ŌåÆ\n   115ŌåÆ### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n   116ŌåÆ\n   117ŌåÆWhen a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n   118ŌåÆ\n   119ŌåÆ**Economics:**\n   120ŌåÆ- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n   121ŌåÆ- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n   122ŌåÆ- Source: platform fee ŌĆö no new fees charged to players\n   123ŌåÆ- Duration: **permanent** ŌĆö referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n   124ŌåÆ- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n   125ŌåÆ\n   126ŌåÆ**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n   127ŌåÆ\n   128ŌåÆ**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer ŌåÆ calculates earnings ŌåÆ inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n   129ŌåÆ\n   130ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   131ŌåÆ- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n   132ŌåÆ- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n   133ŌåÆ- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n   134ŌåÆ- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql ŌĆö referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n   135ŌåÆ- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n   136ŌåÆ\n   137ŌåÆ### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n   138ŌåÆ\n   139ŌåÆReferrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n   140ŌåÆ\n   141ŌåÆ**Stats view:**\n   142ŌåÆ- Total referred players\n   143ŌåÆ- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n   144ŌåÆ- Total wager volume from referrals\n   145ŌåÆ- Total earnings (all time)\n   146ŌåÆ- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n   147ŌåÆ- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n   148ŌåÆ\n   149ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   150ŌåÆ- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   151ŌåÆ- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n   152ŌåÆ- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n   153ŌåÆ- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n   154ŌåÆ\n   155ŌåÆ### FR-6: Claim Flow\n   156ŌåÆ\n   157ŌåÆReferrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n   158ŌåÆ\n   159ŌåÆ**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" ŌåÆ backend validates balance > minimum threshold ŌåÆ creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction ŌåÆ returns 202 with claim ID ŌåÆ frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` ŌåÆ queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature ŌåÆ claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) ŌåÆ frontend shows final state.\n   160ŌåÆ\n   161ŌåÆ**Claim state machine:**\n   162ŌåÆ`pending -> processing -> completed`\n   163ŌåÆ`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n   164ŌåÆ\n   165ŌåÆ**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n   166ŌåÆ\n   167ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   168ŌåÆ- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n   169ŌåÆ- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n   170ŌåÆ- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n   171ŌåÆ- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql ŌĆö referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n   172ŌåÆ- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n   173ŌåÆ- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n   174ŌåÆ- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n   175ŌåÆ- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5sŌåÆ30sŌåÆ300s) for all event types -->\n   176ŌåÆ\n   177ŌåÆ### FR-7: API Contract\n   178ŌåÆ\n   179ŌåÆAll referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n   180ŌåÆ\n   181ŌåÆ**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n   182ŌåÆ`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n   183ŌåÆ\n   184ŌåÆ```\n   185ŌåÆPOST /referral/code                ŌĆö Set referral code\n   186ŌåÆ  Body: { code: string }\n   187ŌåÆ  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n   188ŌåÆ\n   189ŌåÆGET  /referral/code                ŌĆö Get current referral code\n   190ŌåÆ  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n   191ŌåÆ\n   192ŌåÆPOST /referral/apply               ŌĆö Apply a referral code to current user\n   193ŌåÆ  Body: { code: string }\n   194ŌåÆ  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n   195ŌåÆ\n   196ŌåÆGET  /referral/stats               ŌĆö Get referral summary stats\n   197ŌåÆ  Response: {\n   198ŌåÆ    referredCount: number,\n   199ŌåÆ    activeCount: number,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3b67986-fd78-4b1a-b5f8-3ba5e0f9fe3d","uuid":"4b2ae79d-2960-470c-97c0-8023d1894c27","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:17:59.616Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"Referred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable ŌĆö every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n\n**Economics:**\n- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n- Fee is charged in full on-chain ŌĆö rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n\n### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n\nWhen a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n\n**Economics:**\n- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n- Source: platform fee ŌĆö no new fees charged to players\n- Duration: **permanent** ŌĆö referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n\n**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n\n**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer ŌåÆ calculates earnings ŌåÆ inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql ŌĆö referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n\n### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n\nReferrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n\n**Stats view:**\n- Total referred players\n- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n- Total wager volume from referrals\n- Total earnings (all time)\n- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n\n### FR-6: Claim Flow\n\nReferrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n\n**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" ŌåÆ backend validates balance > minimum threshold ŌåÆ creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction ŌåÆ returns 202 with claim ID ŌåÆ frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` ŌåÆ queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature ŌåÆ claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) ŌåÆ frontend shows final state.\n\n**Claim state machine:**\n`pending -> processing -> completed`\n`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n\n**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql ŌĆö referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5sŌåÆ30sŌåÆ300s) for all event types -->\n\n### FR-7: API Contract\n\nAll referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n\n**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n\n```\nPOST /referral/code                ŌĆö Set referral code\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n\nGET  /referral/code                ŌĆö Get current referral code\n  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n\nPOST /referral/apply               ŌĆö Apply a referral code to current user\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n\nGET  /referral/stats               ŌĆö Get referral summary stats\n  Response: {\n    referredCount: number,\n    activeCount: number,","numLines":100,"startLine":100,"totalLines":715}}}
