{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PeXKRMSCHmkTGgKuRxSjDn","type":"tool_result","content":"   350ŌåÆ   - \"Change code\" link ŌåÆ inline edit field to set a new custom code ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n   351ŌåÆ\n   352ŌåÆ2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   353ŌåÆ   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   354ŌåÆ   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   355ŌåÆ   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports ŌåÆ SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   356ŌåÆ   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   357ŌåÆ\n   358ŌåÆ3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   359ŌåÆ   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   360ŌåÆ   - \"Claim\" button ŌĆö enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   361ŌåÆ   - Claim flow: button ŌåÆ loading state ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/claim` ŌåÆ success toast with tx link ŌåÆ refresh stats\n   362ŌåÆ   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   363ŌåÆ\n   364ŌåÆ4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   365ŌåÆ   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   366ŌåÆ   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   367ŌåÆ   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   368ŌåÆ   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   369ŌåÆ\n   370ŌåÆ**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   371ŌåÆ\n   372ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   373ŌåÆ- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   374ŌåÆ- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n   375ŌåÆ- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   376ŌåÆ- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   377ŌåÆ- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378ŌåÆ- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379ŌåÆ- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380ŌåÆ- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381ŌåÆ- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382ŌåÆ- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383ŌåÆ\n   384ŌåÆ#### 9d. Profile Settings ŌĆö Referral Code Input\n   385ŌåÆ\n   386ŌåÆIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   387ŌåÆ\n   388ŌåÆ**Layout:**\n   389ŌåÆ- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   390ŌåÆ- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   391ŌåÆ- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   392ŌåÆ- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   393ŌåÆ\n   394ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   395ŌåÆ- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   396ŌåÆ- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   397ŌåÆ- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   398ŌåÆ- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399ŌåÆ- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   400ŌåÆ\n   401ŌåÆ#### 9e. API Client ŌĆö `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   402ŌåÆ\n   403ŌåÆThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   404ŌåÆ\n   405ŌåÆ```typescript\n   406ŌåÆconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   407ŌåÆ\n   408ŌåÆexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   409ŌåÆexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   410ŌåÆexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   411ŌåÆexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   412ŌåÆexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   413ŌåÆexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   414ŌåÆexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   415ŌåÆ```\n   416ŌåÆ\n   417ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   418ŌåÆ- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   419ŌåÆ- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   420ŌåÆ- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   421ŌåÆ- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422ŌåÆ\n   423ŌåÆ#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook ŌĆö `useReferralApply`\n   424ŌåÆ\n   425ŌåÆA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   426ŌåÆ\n   427ŌåÆ```typescript\n   428ŌåÆ// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   429ŌåÆexport function useReferralApply() {\n   430ŌåÆ  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   431ŌåÆ  const { address } = useWallet();\n   432ŌåÆ\n   433ŌåÆ  useEffect(() => {\n   434ŌåÆ    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   435ŌåÆ    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   436ŌåÆ    if (!stored) return;\n   437ŌåÆ    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   438ŌåÆ    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   439ŌåÆ      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   440ŌåÆ      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   441ŌåÆ  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   442ŌåÆ}\n   443ŌåÆ```\n   444ŌåÆ\n   445ŌåÆMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   446ŌåÆ\n   447ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   448ŌåÆ- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   449ŌåÆ- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   450ŌåÆ- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   451ŌåÆ- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) ŌĆö retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452ŌåÆ- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453ŌåÆ- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454ŌåÆ\n   455ŌåÆ### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   456ŌåÆ\n   457ŌåÆThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   458ŌåÆ\n   459ŌåÆ**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   460ŌåÆ1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   461ŌåÆ2. If referrer exists ŌåÆ calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports ├Ś referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports ├Ś fee_bps / 10000)\n   462ŌåÆ3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   463ŌåÆ4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   464ŌåÆ\n   465ŌåÆ**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   466ŌåÆ1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   467ŌåÆ2. If found ŌåÆ use KOL rate\n   468ŌåÆ3. If not ŌåÆ use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   469ŌåÆ\n   470ŌåÆ**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   471ŌåÆ\n   472ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   473ŌåÆ- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   474ŌåÆ- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   475ŌåÆ- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   476ŌåÆ- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   477ŌåÆ- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   478ŌåÆ- [ ] No additional RPC calls ŌĆö purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   479ŌåÆ- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n   480ŌåÆ\n   481ŌåÆ---\n   482ŌåÆ\n   483ŌåÆ### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   484ŌåÆ\n   485ŌåÆReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   486ŌåÆ\n   487ŌåÆ**Event types (v1):**\n   488ŌåÆ- `referral.claim_requested` ŌĆö emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   489ŌåÆ\n   490ŌåÆNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings ŌĆö only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   491ŌåÆ\n   492ŌåÆ**Payload contract:**\n   493ŌåÆ\n   494ŌåÆ`referral.claim_requested`\n   495ŌåÆ```json\n   496ŌåÆ{\n   497ŌåÆ  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n   498ŌåÆ  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n   499ŌåÆ  \"amountLamports\": \"string\","}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3b67986-fd78-4b1a-b5f8-3ba5e0f9fe3d","uuid":"d35a27b4-9999-434b-8a3d-402e5f2f45fd","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:18:07.931Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"   - \"Change code\" link ŌåÆ inline edit field to set a new custom code ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports ŌåÆ SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button ŌĆö enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button ŌåÆ loading state ŌåÆ calls `POST /referral/claim` ŌåÆ success toast with tx link ŌåÆ refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings ŌĆö Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9e. API Client ŌĆö `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook ŌĆö `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) ŌĆö retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists ŌåÆ calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports ├Ś referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports ├Ś fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found ŌåÆ use KOL rate\n3. If not ŌåÆ use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls ŌĆö purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` ŌĆö emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings ŌĆö only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{\n  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",","numLines":150,"startLine":350,"totalLines":715}}}
