{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SNxkUXgA9HRFoqpMwoqbNK","type":"tool_result","content":"   500ŌåÆ  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n   501ŌåÆ}\n   502ŌåÆ```\n   503ŌåÆ\n   504ŌåÆ**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n   505ŌåÆ\n   506ŌåÆ**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   507ŌåÆ- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n   508ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n   509ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   510ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   511ŌåÆ- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   512ŌåÆ- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   513ŌåÆ\n   514ŌåÆ---\n   515ŌåÆ\n   516ŌåÆ## Design Decisions (v1)\n   517ŌåÆ\n   518ŌåÆ### Why immutable referrer linkage\n   519ŌåÆ\n   520ŌåÆ- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n   521ŌåÆ- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n   522ŌåÆ- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n   523ŌåÆ\n   524ŌåÆ### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n   525ŌåÆ\n   526ŌåÆ- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n   527ŌåÆ- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n   528ŌåÆ- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n   529ŌåÆ\n   530ŌåÆ### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n   531ŌåÆ\n   532ŌåÆ- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n   533ŌåÆ- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n   534ŌåÆ- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n   535ŌåÆ\n   536ŌåÆ---\n   537ŌåÆ\n   538ŌåÆ## Success Criteria\n   539ŌåÆ\n   540ŌåÆ- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n   541ŌåÆ- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   542ŌåÆ- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n   543ŌåÆ- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n   544ŌåÆ- No on-chain program changes required ŌĆö entirely off-chain for v1\n   545ŌåÆ- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n   546ŌåÆ- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n   547ŌåÆ\n   548ŌåÆ---\n   549ŌåÆ\n   550ŌåÆ## Dependencies\n   551ŌåÆ\n   552ŌåÆ- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n   553ŌåÆ- **Async event queue (spec 301)** ŌĆö referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n   554ŌåÆ- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n   555ŌåÆ- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n   556ŌåÆ- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n   557ŌåÆ- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n   558ŌåÆ\n   559ŌåÆ## Assumptions\n   560ŌåÆ\n   561ŌåÆ- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n   562ŌåÆ- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n   563ŌåÆ- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n   564ŌåÆ- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n   565ŌåÆ- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ ŌĆö already met)\n   566ŌåÆ\n   567ŌåÆ---\n   568ŌåÆ\n   569ŌåÆ## Validation Plan\n   570ŌåÆ\n   571ŌåÆ| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   572ŌåÆ|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   573ŌåÆ| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n   574ŌåÆ| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n   575ŌåÆ| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n   576ŌåÆ| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n   577ŌåÆ| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n   578ŌåÆ| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n   579ŌåÆ| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n   580ŌåÆ| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n   581ŌåÆ| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n   582ŌåÆ| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n   583ŌåÆ| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n   584ŌåÆ| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n   585ŌåÆ| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim ŌåÆ poll status ŌåÆ verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n   586ŌåÆ| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code ŌåÆ verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n   587ŌåÆ| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n   588ŌåÆ| 13 | 